    "content": "nullReport and Reduce Your Carbon Footprint with Net Zero Cloud\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Report and Reduce Your Carbon Footprint with Net Zero Cloud\n Get Ready to Use Net Zero Cloud\n Determine the Sources to Inventory\n Emissions Factors That Affect Calculations\n Create Your Consumption Records\n Manage Scope 3 Value Chain Data\n Manage Your Carbon Footprint\n Manage Your Water Footprint\n Create a Water Activity Record\n Create a Water Footprint Record\n Manage the Annual Emissions Inventory\n Record Locking and Recalculation\n Benchmark Building Energy Intensity Data\n Manage Carbon Footprint Data Gaps\n Set Emissions Targets\n Emissions Forecasting\n Carbon Accounting for Extended Organizational Boundaries\n Carbon Accounting for Partner Community Users\n Engage Suppliers for Emissions Reduction\n Allocate Carbon Credits to Offset Unavoidable Emissions\n Allocate Energy Attribute Certificate Credits to Reduce Scope 2...\n Report Social and Governance Data with Net Zero Cloud\n Generate Disclosures by Using Disclosure and Compliance Hub\n Data Collection\n Improve Decarbonization Strategy with Sustainability Programs\n Data Auditing\n Submit Records for Approval\n Use Net Zero Analytics App\n Use DEI Analytics App\n Report Your Carbon Footprint\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nREPORT AND REDUCE YOUR CARBON FOOTPRINT WITH NET ZERO CLOUD\nManage Your Water Footprint\n\nWater footprinting maps and measures the amount of water withdrawn, consumed, or discharged by stationary sources. You can manage your organization’s water footprint for reporting to local bodies or for corporate requirements, and strategize better with actionable data.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions\n\nHere's an image that shows the high-level steps to manage your water footprint:\n\nAs a Net Zero Cloud Manager, you:\n\nRecord the stationary assets and their types.\nRecord all of your organization’s water-related activities, such as withdrawal, consumption, or discharge of water. For more information, see Create a Water Activity Record.\nEnter the water-related risks that exist for your organization.\nCalculate the stationary asset water footprint based on the total volume of water from the associated water activities. Also, the water footprint quantifies the intensity of these activities. For more information, see Create a Water Footprint Record.\nCreate a Water Activity Record\nCreate a record for all of your water-related activities, such as withdrawal, consumption, or discharge of water that is related to your stationary assets.\nCreate a Water Footprint Record\nCreate a record for the total volume of water from your water-related activities, such as withdrawal, consumption, or discharge that are related to your stationary assets. Additionally, water footprints quantify the intensity of these activities using the aggregated water activity records.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
